Today marks a whole year since Russia declared war with Ukraine on February 24, 2022. There have been tensions between the two countries for decades, but 12 months ago things finally came to a head and Russian leader Vladimir Putin ordered soldiers to invade. Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelensky insists his country is standing firm, and this week the UK’s defence secretary warned the conflict is unlikely to end any time soon because Putin ‘won’t stop’. So much has happened over the last year, so Metro.co.uk has put together a summary of all the key events in a helpful timeline below. Here’s everything you need to know about what has happened in the Russia-Ukraine war so far. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.